{"ts": "2026-06-09T00:13:09.703152+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Here's a walkthrough of the three database migrations in this repository, in the order they'd be applied:\n\n---\n\n### Migration 001 — `001_create_users.sql`\n\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE users (\n    id           BIGSERIAL PRIMARY KEY,\n    email        TEXT UNIQUE NOT NULL,\n    display_name TEXT,\n    created_at   TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()\n);\n```\n\n**What it does:** Creates the foundational `users` table with four columns:\n- `id` — An auto-incrementing 64-bit integer used as the primary key.\n- `email` — A required, unique text field (so no two users can share an email).\n- `display_name` — An optional text field for a human-readable name.\n- `created_at` — A timezone-aware timestamp that defaults to the time the row is inserted.\n\nThis is the base table that everything else references.\n\n---\n\n### Migration 002 — `002_create_sessions.sql`\n\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE sessions (\n    id          UUID PRIMARY KEY,\n    user_id     BIGINT NOT NULL REFERENCES users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,\n    issued_at   TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),\n    expires_at  TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL\n);\n```\n\n**What it does:** Creates a `sessions` table for tracking user login/authentication sessions:\n- `id` — A UUID serving as the primary key (common for session tokens).\n- `user_id` — A foreign key referencing `users.id`. The `ON DELETE CASCADE` clause means if a user is deleted, all their sessions are automatically cleaned up.\n- `issued_at` — When the session was created (defaults to now).\n- `expires_at` — When the session should be considered invalid.\n\n---\n\n### Migration 003 — `003_add_session_index.sql`\n\n```sql\nCREATE INDEX idx_sessions_user_id ON sessions(user_id);\n```\n\n**What it does:** Adds a B-tree index on the `sessions.user_id` column. This speeds up lookups like \"find all sessions for a given user\" or join queries between `users` and `sessions`. Without this index, every such query would require a full table scan of `sessions`.\n\n---\n\n### Summary\n\n| Order | Migration | Action |\n|-------|-----------|--------|\n| 1st | `001_create_users` | Creates the `users` table (the core entity) |\n| 2nd | `002_create_sessions` | Creates the `sessions` table with a foreign key to `users` |\n| 3rd | `003_add_session_index` | Adds an index on `sessions.user_id` for query performance |\n\nThe migrations tell a straightforward story: the app has user accounts with email-based identity, and it manages authentication sessions with expiry. The third migration is a performance optimization — likely added after the sessions table started growing and queries on `user_id` became a bottleneck.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 632, "prompt_tokens": 6272, "total_tokens": 6904, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 20, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 5760, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.000793296, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.000243456, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00054984}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780963970-ynVgjy8dN4O27r0xy9ll", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea9b9-8d0d-7770-8628-5ad5b46d6f75-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 6272, "output_tokens": 632, "total_tokens": 6904, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 5760}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 20}}}}]}}}
